				\begin{document}$$\beta$$\end{document} reduces the rheological features, resulting in a faster shearing along the surface [60, 61]. At the wall, the Casson–Maxwell nanofluid had the highest NG\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
